SIMPLE: uncase
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncase
<hw>Un*case"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>case</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To take out of a case or covering; to remove a case
or covering from; to uncover.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To strip; to flay.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>To display, or spread to view, as
a flag, or the colors of a military body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncastle</ent>⟦br⟧
